    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.32.24-25_0001a" />
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                Skyrim Farm             <hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT</hi>
                    <lb/>
                Route 7
                    <lb/>
                Columbia, Mo.
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>June 8, '61</dateline>
                
                
                <salute>Dear Slade:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>We must have been thinking of each other at the same time. Our letters crossed. I was very glad to hear from you, for it seemed suddenly that I had not written you for a long while.</p>
                
                <p>I've just received a telegram announcing that the Nebraska Legislature has today voted <hi rend="underline">unanimously</hi> to place a bronze bust of me permanently
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.32.24-25_0001b"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    <fw type="curatorial"><del/></fw>
                    
                    in the Hall of Fame located in the State Capitol Building in Lincoln! This is a sort of triumph, as the Bill establishing the Hall of Fame, stipulates that no living person shall be elected.</p>
                
                <p>There was a state-wide agreement that exception should be made in my case! Up to date, it seems that the late Senator George <del>W. Norris</del> W. Norris is the only other to be so honored. (I'll bet Buffalo Bill
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">24</fw>
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.32.24-25_0002"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>
                    
                    will, sooner or later, be honored; He should be.)</p>
                
                <p>It's going to be bully to see you</p>
                
                <p>Affectionate thoughts for you and Nita. (I wish I could run in on you for an hour or so, in the evening now &amp; then!)</p>
                <closer>
                <signed>John N.</signed> 
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
